ly Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English: variant of   Bowell  , with post-medieval excrescent <i>-s</i>."],"variants":[{"name":"Bowell","meanings":["English (of Norman origin): habitational name from Bouelles in Seine-Maritime, France, so named with Old Norman French <i>boelle</i> ‘enclosure, dwelling’."]},{"name":"Boals","meanings":["English: either a variant of   Bowles   or a variant of   Boal  , with excrescent <i>-s</i>."]}]},{"name":"William","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Probably the most successful of all the Old French names of Germanic origin that were introduced to England by the Normans. It is derived from Germanic <i>wil</i> ‘will, desire’ + <i>helm</i> ‘helmet, protection’. The fact that it was borne by the Conqueror himself does not seem to have inhibited its favour with the ‘conquered’ population: in the first century after the Conquest it was the commonest male name of all, and not only among the Normans. In the later Middle Ages it was overtaken by   John  , but continued to run second to that name until the 20th century, when the picture became more fragmented."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705191,"age":17,"year":"1315","toYear":"1317","julianDay":2201354,"title":"Famine Strikes Europe","description":"A famine caused by cold winters and wet summers across Europe caused millions to die due to starvation. Desperation from hunger caused high levels of crime, stampedes in bread lines in London, infanticide, and even cannibalism throughout Europe.","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705192,"age":30,"year":"1328","julianDay":2206102,"title":"First War of Scottish Independence","description":"The First War of Scottish Independence began after England invaded Scotland in 1296. The Treaty of Edinburgh was signed in 1328 which declared peace between the two kingdoms and brought the war to an end.","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705193,"age":39,"year":"1337","toYear":"1453","julianDay":2209390,"title":"The Hundred Years' War","description":"The Hundred Years' War between France and England was largely due to the question of legitimate succession to the French crown.","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"When William Boweles III was born in 1298, in Rushall, Staffordshire, England, his father, William De Boweles II, was 20 and his mother, Agnes Hambury, was 17. He married Elizabeth De Giffard in 1326. They were the parents of at least 1 daughter. He died in 1348, in his hometown, at the age of 50."},"et":{"1298–1348":"1298–1348","–1328":"–1328","1328–1385":"1328–1385","1278–1347":"1278–1347","1281–1326":"1281–1326","1385":"1385","1281":"1281","1326":"1326","1348":"1348","1337":"1337","1315":"1315","1347":"1347","after 1328":"pärast 1328","1278":"1278","1453":"1453","1298":"1298","1328":"1328","1317":"1317","Rushall, Staffordshire, England":"Rushall, Staffordshire, England","Rushall, Staffordshire, England, United Kingdom":"Rushall, Staffordshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1298–1348":"1298–1348","–1328":"–1328","1328–1385":"1328–1385","1278–1347":"1278–1347","1281–1326":"1281–1326","1385":"1385","1281":"1281","1326":"1326","1348":"1348","1337":"1337","1315":"1315","1347":"1347","after 1328":"1328 jälkeen","1278":"1278","1453":"1453","1298":"1298","1328":"1328","1317":"1317","Rushall, Staffordshire, England":"Rushall, Staffordshire, England","Rushall, Staffordshire, England, United Kingdom":"Rushall, Staffordshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"1298–1348":"1298–1348","–1328":"–1328","1328–1385":"1328–1385","1278–1347":"1278–1347","1281–1326":"1281–1326","1385":"1385","1281":"1281","1326":"1326","1348":"1348","1337":"1337","1315":"1315","1347":"1347","after 1328":"après 1328","1278":"1278","1453":"1453","1298":"1298","1328":"1328","1317":"1317","Rushall, Staffordshire, England":"Rushall, Staffordshire, Angleterre","Rushall, Staffordshire, England, United Kingdom":"Rushall, Staffords